<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>9 SPEED AND 11 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RTO-1X707LL/DLL/MLL AND RTO-1X709MLL MODELS - REMOVE - OUTPUT
        YOKE/COMPANION FLANGE
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="5">
        <title>OUTPUT YOKE/COMPANION FLANGE</title>
        <para>The shifter housing must be removed to lock the transmission.</para>
        <para>After removal of the output yoke/companion flange, temporarily replace the output shaft nut to protect the
            output shaft threads during auxiliary section disassembly.
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Engage two (2) mainshaft sliding clutches into two (2) mainshaft gears to lock the
                transmission (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302019">Figure 19</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302019" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302019" filename="../figg13/G1302019.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 19. Mainshaft Sliding Clutches</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a large breaker bar or air impact wrench to remove the output shaft nut (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302020">Figure 20</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302020" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302020" filename="../figg13/G1302020.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 20. Remove Output Shaft Nut</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Pull the yoke or flange straight to the rear and off the output shaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302021">Figure 21</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302021" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302021" filename="../figg13/G1302021.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 21. Pull Yoke</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the slinger (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302022">Figure 22</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302022" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302022" filename="../figg13/G1302022.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 22. Remove Slinger</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the speedometer gear or spacer (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302023">Figure 23</hotlnk>)
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302023" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302023" filename="../figg13/G1302023.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 23. Speedometer Gear</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
